HEADWORD: Coalsack
<hw>Coal"sack`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Coal</ets> +
2d <ets>sack</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>Any one of the
spaces in the Milky Way which are very black, owing to the nearly
complete absence of stars; esp., the large space near the Southern Cross
sometimes called the <altname>Black Magellanic
Cloud</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coal tar</ent>⟦br⟧
